1
00:01:07,234 --> 00:01:09,028
Inside a snowflake,

2
00:01:09,111 --> 00:01:11,322
like the one on your sleeve,

3
00:01:11,405 --> 00:01:14,992
there happened a story
you must see to believe.

4
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:35,846
Way up in the mountains,
in the high range of Pontoos,

5
00:01:36,180 --> 00:01:38,015
lay the small town of Whoville,

6
00:01:39,350 --> 00:01:40,976
the home of the Whos!

7
00:01:45,564 --> 00:01:48,400
Ask any Who, and they'll have this to say,

8
00:01:48,526 --> 00:01:52,530
"There is no place
like Whoville around Christmas Day."

9
00:01:53,364 --> 00:01:56,325
Every window was flocked,
every lamppost was dressed,

10
00:01:56,408 --> 00:02:00,746
and the Whoville Band marched
in their Christmas-y best.

11
00:02:05,709 --> 00:02:08,420
Merry Christmas!
Merry Christmas!

12
00:02:21,684 --> 00:02:24,520
Arbor Day was fine,
and Easter was pleasant,

13
00:02:24,562 --> 00:02:27,940
and every Saint Fizzin's Day
they ate a Fizz pheasant,

14
00:02:28,065 --> 00:02:31,986
but every Who knew,
from their 12 toes to their snout,

15
00:02:32,069 --> 00:02:34,280
they loved Christmas the most,

16
00:02:34,363 --> 00:02:36,448
without a single Who doubt.

17
00:02:41,203 --> 00:02:43,414
- Farfingle's welcomes you!
- Thank you.

18
00:02:43,497 --> 00:02:47,042
Merry Christmas! Thank you
for shopping Farfingle's!

19
00:02:47,710 --> 00:02:50,004
We got a snoozlephone
for your brother Drew,

20
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:52,715
and a snoozlephone for your brother Stu,

21
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:56,260
a muncle for your uncle, a fant for your aunt,

22
00:02:56,302 --> 00:02:58,762
and a fandpa for your Cousin Leon.

23
00:02:59,013 --> 00:03:01,307
So, we just need... Cindy?

24
00:03:01,432 --> 00:03:02,766
Sale on aisle three!

25
00:03:02,808 --> 00:03:04,810
- Cindy Lou! Cin... Oh.
- Merry Christmas!

26
00:03:04,894 --> 00:03:06,604
Oh, hello, Myrna. Merry Christmas, Fred.

27
00:03:06,687 --> 00:03:08,939
Excuse me one minute. Cindy Lou? Honey?

28
00:03:10,441 --> 00:03:11,483
- Dad?
- Yeah?

29
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:13,444
Doesn't this seem like a bit much?

30
00:03:14,403 --> 00:03:17,615
This is what Christmas is all about!
Can't you feel it?

31
00:03:17,907 --> 00:03:19,199
Merry Christmas!

32
00:03:19,283 --> 00:03:21,785
Thank you for shopping... Wait a second!

33
00:03:21,827 --> 00:03:24,246
- Don't forget your change!
- Another minute closer to Christmas!

34
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:30,961
For the next five minutes only, 99 % off!

35
00:03:43,849 --> 00:03:48,604
Yes, every Who
down in Whoville liked Christmas a lot,

36
00:03:49,104 --> 00:03:52,858
but the Grinch, who lived
just north of Whoville,

37
00:03:53,817 --> 00:03:55,110
did not.

38
00:03:58,489 --> 00:04:00,824
Hi, girls.
All the good mistletoe's at the top.

39
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:02,993
Hey, Drew!
I'll race you!

40
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,662
Not if I race you first.

41
00:04:04,703 --> 00:04:07,706
Last one to the top's a stinky old Grinch!

42
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,669
You guys, where are we?

43
00:04:12,002 --> 00:04:16,006
- I think we should go back.
- What? You're scared of the Grinch!

44
00:04:16,548 --> 00:04:20,469
- No!
- They say he lives up here in a big cave.

45
00:04:20,719 --> 00:04:23,472
And he only comes down
when he's hungry for the taste of

46
00:04:23,681 --> 00:04:25,349
- Who flesh!
- Oh, Drew!

47
00:04:25,474 --> 00:04:28,686
- Guys!
- STU: You're scared of the Grinch!

48
00:04:28,727 --> 00:04:30,354
You're scared of the Grinch!

49
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:32,856
Are too!

50
00:04:32,898 --> 00:04:34,108
- Am not!
- Are too!

51
00:04:37,027 --> 00:04:38,195
Wait for me!

52
00:04:49,373 --> 00:04:51,709
Can we touch it? Touch the door?

53
00:04:51,917 --> 00:04:53,627
Do it for me, Stu.

54
00:05:00,259 --> 00:05:01,385
Drew?

55
00:05:26,035 --> 00:05:27,745
Well done, Max!

56
00:05:28,495 --> 00:05:31,248
Serves them right, those yuletide-loving

57
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:34,877
sickly-sweet, nog-sucking cheer mongers!

58
00:05:36,503 --> 00:05:40,966
I really don't like 'em.
Mmm-mmm. No, I don't.

59
00:05:44,303 --> 00:05:45,429
Max!

60
00:05:47,306 --> 00:05:49,516
Get my cloak!

61
00:05:50,517 --> 00:05:53,645
I've been much too tolerant
of these "Who-venile" delinquents

62
00:05:53,729 --> 00:05:55,939
and their innocent, victimless pranks.

63
00:05:57,733 --> 00:06:00,444
So, they wanna get to know me, do they?

64
00:06:01,111 --> 00:06:04,323
They want to spend a little
quality time with the Grinch.

65
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:10,079
I guess I could use a little social interaction.

66
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:21,131
Merry Christmas!

67
00:06:21,215 --> 00:06:24,676
Oh, yeah, you bet. Ho, ho, ho, and stuff.

68
00:06:28,222 --> 00:06:31,642
Oh, my. Someone has
vandalized that vehicle.

69
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:34,895
You see, Max? The city is a dangerous place.

70
00:06:34,978 --> 00:06:37,773
The Grinch hated Christmas,
the whole Christmas season.

71
00:06:37,815 --> 00:06:39,024
Top of the day, flatfoot.

72
00:06:39,108 --> 00:06:42,486
Now, please, don't ask why.
No one quite knows the reason.

73
00:06:42,528 --> 00:06:43,987
Hey, kids. Here's a present for ya.

74
00:06:44,071 --> 00:06:47,491
Be sure to run real fast with it, now.
Come on. Double time. Let's go. Move.

75
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:50,494
It could be that his head
wasn't screwed on just right,

76
00:06:50,577 --> 00:06:53,956
or it could be, perhaps,
that his shoes were too tight.

77
00:06:53,997 --> 00:06:55,833
But I think that the most likely reason of all...

78
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:57,000
- Merry Christmas!
- Idiot.

79
00:06:57,042 --> 00:07:00,879
...may have been
that his heart was two sizes too small.

80
00:07:01,463 --> 00:07:04,383
Hey, stranger,
won't let you go till you buy a chapeau!

81
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:16,562
The streets are filled
with Christmas cheer

82
00:07:16,687 --> 00:07:18,730
Boy, nothing beats Christmas, right?

83
00:07:19,565 --> 00:07:20,691
I guess.

84
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:23,861
- You guess?
- Well, it's just

85
00:07:23,944 --> 00:07:28,031
I look around at you and Mom
and everyone getting all kerbobbled.

86
00:07:28,365 --> 00:07:31,034
Doesn't this seem superfluous?

87
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:35,080
Dad! Dad!

88
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:40,127
- What happened to you?
- It was the Grinch!

89
00:07:45,591 --> 00:07:48,051
- Grinch?
- What do you want? I mean...

90
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:49,720
Grinch? Oh, no!

91
00:07:51,221 --> 00:07:53,932
Did someone just say, "Grinch"?

92
00:07:55,017 --> 00:07:56,643
Hello, Mayor May Who, sir.

93
00:07:59,897 --> 00:08:01,023
Lou?

94
00:08:05,235 --> 00:08:07,946
I don't need to remind you
that this Christmas marks

95
00:08:08,030 --> 00:08:10,741
the one thousandth Whobilation.

96
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:15,871
- Whoville's most important celebration!
- And The Book of Who says,

97
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:16,997
very clearly,

98
00:08:18,457 --> 00:08:20,751
"Every size of Who we can measure

99
00:08:20,876 --> 00:08:24,838
"knows that Whobilation is
a time we must treasure!"

100
00:08:24,922 --> 00:08:28,008
Now, Lou, please tell me that your boys

101
00:08:28,342 --> 00:08:30,260
were not up on Mount Crumpit

102
00:08:30,344 --> 00:08:34,223
provoking the one creature
within a billion bilometers of here

103
00:08:34,264 --> 00:08:36,475
- who hates Christmas!
- But it was the Grinch!

104
00:08:38,393 --> 00:08:41,647
No, no, no, no, sir,
the boys didn't see any Grinch.

105
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:46,151
They just... I think they were
up on the mountain

106
00:08:46,235 --> 00:08:48,820
playing with matches,
or defacing public property, or...

107
00:08:48,904 --> 00:08:50,197
Oh, well.

108
00:08:50,822 --> 00:08:52,532
That's a relief.

109
00:08:52,616 --> 00:08:57,454
All right, you heard the man,
there's no Grinch problem here.

110
00:09:05,504 --> 00:09:07,130
Lou,
I need it there by tomorrow.

111
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:08,966
Heckuvarush.

112
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:11,510
Merry Christmas, Mo. Next in line.

113
00:09:14,638 --> 00:09:17,724
But, Dad. I just don't understand something.

114
00:09:18,225 --> 00:09:20,435
Why won't anyone talk about the Grinch?

115
00:09:21,311 --> 00:09:23,230
You kids and the Grinch!

116
00:09:23,897 --> 00:09:27,734
You see, Cindy,
the Grinch is a Who who always...

117
00:09:28,151 --> 00:09:31,738
Actually, not a Who, he's more of a...

118
00:09:31,822 --> 00:09:34,908
- A what?
- Exactly, honey.

119
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:38,203
And he's a What who doesn't like Christmas.

120
00:09:39,162 --> 00:09:41,039
Take a look at his mailbox, sweetie.

121
00:09:41,123 --> 00:09:45,043
Not a single Christmas card, in or out, ever!

122
00:09:45,877 --> 00:09:48,797
- But why?
- MAN 2: Lou, where's my mail? Lou!

123
00:09:48,839 --> 00:09:53,302
- Got the wrong mail here.
- Lou! I got the wrong mail!

124
00:09:55,095 --> 00:09:58,181
- I'll be right there.
- MAN 1: Lou, we got a problem!

125
00:09:58,223 --> 00:10:00,642
All right, we'll straighten this out.

126
00:10:04,146 --> 00:10:06,940
It'll take them years
to sort this out.

127
00:10:07,024 --> 00:10:10,569
This is his and now
it's yours, and this hers and now it's his!

128
00:10:13,155 --> 00:10:15,240
And for the rest of you...

129
00:10:16,825 --> 00:10:19,036
Jury duty! Jury duty! Jury duty!

130
00:10:19,077 --> 00:10:21,872
Blackmail. Pink slip.
Chain letter. Eviction notice.

131
00:10:21,997 --> 00:10:23,707
Jury duty...

132
00:10:28,462 --> 00:10:32,549
Would you mind helping me
take this to the back room, honey?

133
00:10:32,716 --> 00:10:35,719
But be careful of the sorting machine, right?

134
00:10:35,802 --> 00:10:38,472
Yeah.

135
00:11:07,584 --> 00:11:08,627
Hmm.

136
00:11:10,504 --> 00:11:11,505
Whew.

137
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:14,424
Gesundheit. Oh.

138
00:11:23,141 --> 00:11:24,810
You're the...

139
00:11:25,102 --> 00:11:27,437
The... The Grinch!

140
00:11:30,607 --> 00:11:33,193
- Well, that worked out nicely.
- Help!

141
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:34,986
Help!

142
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:47,207
- Help me! Somebody!
- GRINCH: Max, let's go.

143
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:50,961
Our work here is finished. Sheesh!

144
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:54,381
Help me! Please help!

145
00:11:54,464 --> 00:11:56,341
That is not a chew toy!

146
00:11:57,050 --> 00:11:59,719
Stop it, Max! Get that out of your mouth!

147
00:11:59,803 --> 00:12:01,555
You have no idea where it's been!

148
00:12:06,393 --> 00:12:07,477
Help!

149
00:12:10,105 --> 00:12:13,984
Bleeding hearts of the world, unite!

150
00:12:17,404 --> 00:12:18,530
There!

151
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:23,994
There! Give me that!

152
00:12:24,286 --> 00:12:27,456
Don't you know you're not supposed to take
things that don't belong to you?

153
00:12:27,497 --> 00:12:29,541
What's the matter with you?
You some kind of wild animal?

154
00:12:32,377 --> 00:12:35,172
- Let's go.
- Thanks for saving me!

155
00:12:42,387 --> 00:12:44,055
Saving you?

156
00:12:45,056 --> 00:12:47,100
Is that what you think I was doing?

157
00:12:47,517 --> 00:12:48,685
Uh-huh.

158
00:12:50,061 --> 00:12:51,688
Wrong-o.

159
00:12:54,232 --> 00:12:58,111
I merely noticed that
you were improperly packaged, my dear.

160
00:12:58,862 --> 00:13:01,406
Drat! Hold still!

161
00:13:02,282 --> 00:13:03,658
Max, pick out a bow.

162
00:13:05,035 --> 00:13:06,912
Can I use your finger for a second?

163
00:13:07,829 --> 00:13:09,789
Hello! Hello!

164
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,504
- Cindy?
- Dad!

165
00:13:17,422 --> 00:13:18,632
Daddy!

166
00:13:19,382 --> 00:13:20,550
Daddy!

167
00:13:21,176 --> 00:13:24,221
What the hey... Honey.

168
00:13:25,722 --> 00:13:26,848
Cindy!

169
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:28,850
Dad! It was amazing!

170
00:13:29,142 --> 00:13:32,229
You've been practicing
your Christmas wrapping!

171
00:13:32,312 --> 00:13:36,399
- Honey, I am so proud of you.
- Oh, well...

172
00:13:36,691 --> 00:13:38,276
Now, that's holiday.

173
00:13:38,401 --> 00:13:41,404
Sweet little Cindy
didn't know what to do.

174
00:13:41,947 --> 00:13:44,908
In her head bum-tumbled a conflict or two.

175
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:48,537
"If the Grinch was so bad,
then why did he save me?"

176
00:13:48,703 --> 00:13:50,247
Maybe he wasn't so bad.

177
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:51,456
Come on, let's go home.

178
00:13:51,540 --> 00:13:53,250
Maybe. Just maybe.

179
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:57,087
I've got the Christmas tree
I've got the melody

180
00:13:58,088 --> 00:14:00,924
No lights on in the house.
Your mom must be shoppin'.

181
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:02,926
Oh, good, I'm so glad
you're home.

182
00:14:03,093 --> 00:14:06,304
Oh, I can feel it, Lou. This is the year.

183
00:14:07,138 --> 00:14:11,768
When everybody asks who has the most
spectacular lights in all of Greater Whoville,

184
00:14:12,769 --> 00:14:16,106
they're gonna cry out, "Mrs. Betty Lou Who!"

185
00:14:16,648 --> 00:14:19,484
Isn't this the chandelier
from the dining room?

186
00:14:19,568 --> 00:14:21,278
It's all for the cause, dear.

187
00:14:21,778 --> 00:14:23,113
- Oh, and Cindy?
- Oh. Yeah.

188
00:14:23,154 --> 00:14:24,948
Could you be Mommy's Little Helper,

189
00:14:24,990 --> 00:14:27,951
and unscrew the bulb there
from the refrigerator?

190
00:14:27,993 --> 00:14:30,495
- 'Cause somehow I missed that one.
- Go on.

191
00:14:34,916 --> 00:14:40,380
Every year Martha May Whovier
has the best lights.

192
00:14:41,464 --> 00:14:43,800
Well, not this year. This year,

193
00:14:44,634 --> 00:14:48,179
I'm gonna beat that prim,
perfect little prissy...

194
00:14:48,263 --> 00:14:49,472
Betty!

195
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:53,101
- Hi!
- Martha!

196
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:57,647
My, I've never seen so many
beautiful Christmas lights, Betty Lou!

197
00:14:58,023 --> 00:15:02,027
Well, I'd blow every fuse
if I tried to keep up with you, Martha May!

198
00:15:02,110 --> 00:15:06,489
Isn't this antique darling? It's handcrafted.

199
00:15:06,531 --> 00:15:08,575
And almost 100 years old.

200
00:15:09,451 --> 00:15:11,328
Jeez. I'm really impressed!

201
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:14,205
This, however, is new.

202
00:15:26,051 --> 00:15:27,844
Whoa up! Hey! Betty, Betty! Sweetie!

203
00:15:44,569 --> 00:15:46,196
Well, good night, Betty.

204
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:51,660
Oh! I got it!

205
00:15:51,701 --> 00:15:53,662
- Honey, honey.
- I've got it. I got it. I...

206
00:15:53,703 --> 00:15:56,039
Hello?

207
00:15:56,122 --> 00:15:58,750
Is my sub-zero chillibrator running?

208
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:02,379
- I suppose.
- Well, you better go catch it!

209
00:16:10,261 --> 00:16:11,846
That's a good one!

210
00:16:12,097 --> 00:16:13,598
That is rich.

211
00:16:16,893 --> 00:16:18,019
Let's go home.

212
00:16:23,024 --> 00:16:26,069
Fleas before beauty. Thank you.

213
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:31,908
Come on, hurry up. Slowpoke.

214
00:16:46,548 --> 00:16:49,718
There's got to be a better way!

215
00:17:11,114 --> 00:17:13,867
A car would have paid for itself by now!

216
00:17:15,994 --> 00:17:18,538
Oh, goody. Another load coming down.

217
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:24,753
Ugh, what's that stench?

218
00:17:25,545 --> 00:17:27,046
It's fantastic!

219
00:17:29,549 --> 00:17:31,176
Max! Grab a bag.

220
00:17:32,302 --> 00:17:33,970
We'll come back for the rest.

221
00:17:34,471 --> 00:17:36,681
Of course, when I say "we," I mean "you."

222
00:17:38,016 --> 00:17:40,977
It's amazing what these
Whos just throw away.

223
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:47,358
Oh, well. One man's toxic sludge
is another man's potpourri.

224
00:17:47,442 --> 00:17:50,111
I don't know. It's some kind of soap.

225
00:18:02,832 --> 00:18:06,252
Where are you, Christmas

226
00:18:06,961 --> 00:18:10,048
Why can't I find you

227
00:18:11,007 --> 00:18:15,678
Why have you gone away

228
00:18:18,848 --> 00:18:22,352
My world is changing

229
00:18:22,977 --> 00:18:26,606
I'm rearranging

230
00:18:26,898 --> 00:18:29,859
Does that mean Christmas

231
00:18:30,443 --> 00:18:35,406
Changes too

232
00:18:42,747 --> 00:18:46,292
Where are you, Christmas

233
00:18:46,876 --> 00:18:49,879
Do you remember

234
00:18:50,672 --> 00:18:55,760
The girl you used to know

235
00:18:57,428 --> 00:18:59,264
You and I

236
00:18:59,347 --> 00:19:02,392
Were so carefree

237
00:19:02,892 --> 00:19:05,854
Now, nothing's easy

238
00:19:06,229 --> 00:19:09,691
Did Christmas change

239
00:19:10,191 --> 00:19:13,778
Or just

240
00:19:16,072 --> 00:19:19,033
Me

241
00:19:47,729 --> 00:19:49,272
Sweet!

242
00:19:59,032 --> 00:20:02,911
Be it ever so heinous

243
00:20:02,952 --> 00:20:07,081
There's no place like home

244
00:20:11,836 --> 00:20:14,088
First floor, factory rejects.

245
00:20:15,632 --> 00:20:17,884
Those Whos are hard to frazzle, Max!

246
00:20:17,967 --> 00:20:21,304
But, we did our worst.
And that's all that matters.

247
00:20:21,346 --> 00:20:25,016
At least I scared the bejeebles out of that
little girl at the post office.

248
00:20:25,141 --> 00:20:27,352
She'll be scarred for life, if we're lucky.

249
00:20:44,327 --> 00:20:46,454
Funny she didn't rat on us, though.

250
00:20:46,496 --> 00:20:48,665
Must be afraid of reprisals.

251
00:21:00,677 --> 00:21:04,514
Yes! Down a size and a half!

