00:41:45,629 --> 00:41:47,255
and be a part of Christmas...

516
00:41:49,883 --> 00:41:53,053
- Grow up!
- Then maybe it'll be all right for me, too!

517
00:41:53,094 --> 00:41:54,721
I'm sorry, your session is over.

518
00:41:54,763 --> 00:41:57,807
Please make another appointment with
the receptionist on the way out.

519
00:41:57,891 --> 00:42:00,185
Please, please. You have to accept the award.

520
00:42:05,774 --> 00:42:06,942
Award?

521
00:42:09,945 --> 00:42:13,073
You never mentioned an award.

522
00:42:13,615 --> 00:42:15,659
Yeah, with a trophy and everything!

523
00:42:15,825 --> 00:42:17,619
- And I won?
- You won!

524
00:42:18,912 --> 00:42:21,456
- That means there were losers.
- I guess.

525
00:42:21,498 --> 00:42:25,919
- So, if you come...
- A town full of losers!

526
00:42:26,461 --> 00:42:27,837
I like it.

527
00:42:28,672 --> 00:42:31,383
Was anyone emotionally shattered?

528
00:42:32,217 --> 00:42:33,885
Come on, a minute ago
I couldn't shut you up!

529
00:42:33,969 --> 00:42:35,470
Details, details!

530
00:42:35,637 --> 00:42:37,973
Well, the Mayor wasn't happy.

531
00:42:38,807 --> 00:42:40,809
Oh! No.

532
00:42:42,143 --> 00:42:43,853
Martha May will be there.

533
00:42:45,689 --> 00:42:47,190
- Oh, she will?
- Mmm-hmm.

534
00:42:48,316 --> 00:42:51,278
And she'll see me. A winner.

535
00:42:52,821 --> 00:42:56,950
She'll be on me like fleegle flies
on a flat-faced floogle horse.

536
00:42:56,992 --> 00:42:59,703
Well, I'm sorry
to disappoint you, Martha baby.

537
00:42:59,786 --> 00:43:01,663
But the "G" train has left the station.

538
00:43:02,122 --> 00:43:03,832
So, will you come?

539
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:05,625
Oh, all right.

540
00:43:07,002 --> 00:43:09,587
I don't know if it's that
adorable twinkle in your eye,

541
00:43:09,671 --> 00:43:11,589
or that nonconformist streak

542
00:43:11,673 --> 00:43:14,884
the reminds me of a younger, less hairy me.

543
00:43:15,427 --> 00:43:17,387
But you've convinced me.

544
00:43:17,512 --> 00:43:18,555
Who knows?

545
00:43:18,638 --> 00:43:22,517
This Whobilation could change
my entire outlook on life!

546
00:43:23,143 --> 00:43:24,853
- Really?
- No.

547
00:43:58,845 --> 00:44:02,849
There you are. Honey.
You can make snow angels later.

548
00:44:03,725 --> 00:44:05,727
We can't be late for the Whobilation!

549
00:44:09,397 --> 00:44:12,400
The nerve of those Whos.
Inviting me down there.

550
00:44:12,484 --> 00:44:14,319
On such short notice.

551
00:44:14,402 --> 00:44:17,947
Even if I wanted to go,
my schedule wouldn't allow it!

552
00:44:20,450 --> 00:44:22,786
"4:00, wallow in self-pity.

553
00:44:23,244 --> 00:44:26,122
"4:30, stare into the abyss.

554
00:44:27,082 --> 00:44:29,084
"5:00, solve world hunger,

555
00:44:29,209 --> 00:44:30,752
"tell no one.

556
00:44:31,336 --> 00:44:33,088
"5:30, Jazzercise.

557
00:44:33,380 --> 00:44:36,424
"6:30, dinner with me."
I can't cancel that again.

558
00:44:36,883 --> 00:44:39,469
"7:00, wrestle with my self-loathing"

559
00:44:40,428 --> 00:44:41,763
I'm booked!

560
00:44:41,888 --> 00:44:43,515
Of course, if I bumped the loathing to 9:00,

561
00:44:43,598 --> 00:44:46,226
I could still be done in time
to lay in bed, stare at the ceiling,

562
00:44:46,267 --> 00:44:48,520
and slip slowly into madness.

563
00:44:49,604 --> 00:44:51,523
But what would I wear?

564
00:45:11,543 --> 00:45:13,795
It's not a dress, it's a kilt!

565
00:45:15,422 --> 00:45:16,756
Sicko!

566
00:45:18,675 --> 00:45:22,470
Stupid. Ugly. Out of date!

567
00:45:24,139 --> 00:45:25,640
This is ridiculous.

568
00:45:25,723 --> 00:45:29,185
If I can't find something
nice to wear, I'm not going.

569
00:45:42,490 --> 00:45:43,491
Oh.

570
00:45:44,200 --> 00:45:45,285
Ah.

571
00:45:46,119 --> 00:45:47,454
Mmm.

572
00:45:47,495 --> 00:45:48,830
That's it, I'm not going.

573
00:46:01,593 --> 00:46:06,181
Well, it's time for our
Holiday Cheermeister of the Year Award!

574
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:15,690
Congratulations, Mr. Grinch!

575
00:46:18,443 --> 00:46:19,694
He isn't here.

576
00:46:20,487 --> 00:46:21,613
What?

577
00:46:22,489 --> 00:46:25,575
He didn't show? Oh.

578
00:46:25,950 --> 00:46:27,911
Who could have predicted this?

579
00:46:29,037 --> 00:46:31,789
All right. I'll swing by for a minute,

580
00:46:31,873 --> 00:46:36,044
allow them to envy me, grab a handful
of popcorn shrimp, and blow out of there.

581
00:46:36,753 --> 00:46:40,715
But what if it's a cruel prank?
What if it's a cash bar?

582
00:46:41,090 --> 00:46:44,677
How dare they? All right, I'll go.

583
00:46:45,053 --> 00:46:48,723
But I'll be fashionably late.
No. Yes. No. Yes. No!

584
00:46:49,057 --> 00:46:50,350
Yes!

585
00:46:51,935 --> 00:46:53,520
Definitely not!

586
00:46:53,853 --> 00:46:56,272
All right. I've made my decision.

587
00:46:56,773 --> 00:46:58,983
I'm going, and that's that.

588
00:47:00,568 --> 00:47:01,861
Had my fingers crossed.

589
00:47:06,074 --> 00:47:08,576
Maybe I should flip a coin!

590
00:47:16,292 --> 00:47:20,672
Well, I guess the award goes
to the runner-up.

591
00:47:22,757 --> 00:47:24,092
That's right.

592
00:47:24,133 --> 00:47:27,095
A man for whom Christmas comes,
not once a year,

593
00:47:27,554 --> 00:47:29,556
but every minute of every day!

594
00:47:29,931 --> 00:47:32,392
A handsome, noble man,

595
00:47:33,017 --> 00:47:35,478
a man who's had his tonsils removed twice!

596
00:47:36,729 --> 00:47:38,606
That's an interesting story.

597
00:47:38,773 --> 00:47:40,775
You see, what happened was...

598
00:47:55,498 --> 00:47:56,833
Hello, Martha.

599
00:47:57,125 --> 00:47:58,167
He made it!

600
00:47:58,251 --> 00:47:59,377
- Cindy...
- Honey!

601
00:48:23,568 --> 00:48:26,029
Boo.

602
00:48:27,238 --> 00:48:28,823
Hot crowd. Hot crowd.

603
00:48:30,742 --> 00:48:32,744
I believe I'm here to

604
00:48:34,829 --> 00:48:37,874
accept an award of some kind?

605
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:41,753
And the child

606
00:48:42,795 --> 00:48:44,088
mentioned a check?

607
00:48:44,505 --> 00:48:47,008
- No, I didn't.
- All right, then, give me the award.

608
00:48:47,050 --> 00:48:49,010
Come on, while I'm young!

609
00:48:49,260 --> 00:48:52,013
Don't you worry, Mr. Holiday Cheermeister,

610
00:48:52,096 --> 00:48:53,681
you'll get your award.

611
00:48:53,723 --> 00:48:57,852
But first, a little family reunion.

612
00:48:58,853 --> 00:49:00,438
They nursed you.

613
00:49:00,521 --> 00:49:03,566
They clothed you. Here they are,

614
00:49:03,650 --> 00:49:06,527
your Old Biddies!

615
00:49:08,196 --> 00:49:10,907
Are you two still living?

616
00:49:11,366 --> 00:49:13,701
- Oh.
- We missed you!

617
00:49:13,785 --> 00:49:16,329
Rose. The sweater. The sweater, Rose.

618
00:49:16,371 --> 00:49:19,165
Sweater? What are you talkin' about?
No, I can't!

619
00:49:19,207 --> 00:49:20,667
I can't do this!

620
00:49:23,211 --> 00:49:24,754
Don't touch me there!

621
00:49:32,970 --> 00:49:35,014
Put him in the Chair of Cheer!

622
00:49:35,056 --> 00:49:37,892
Chair of Cheer? What's the Chair of Cheer?

623
00:49:39,185 --> 00:49:43,439
- You didn't tell me about the Chair of Cheer!
- Please, Mr. Grinch. Please?

624
00:49:44,774 --> 00:49:48,111
No, no, no. I can't do it. Honestly.
I'm not ready. It's too much, too soon!

625
00:49:48,194 --> 00:49:49,821
It's that time of year.

626
00:49:49,904 --> 00:49:53,491
The Cheermeister's ride
in the Chair of Cheer!

627
00:49:53,574 --> 00:49:56,828
Put me down! I mean it! I've got a lawyer.

628
00:49:57,245 --> 00:49:59,247
There'll be hell to pay!

629
00:50:00,623 --> 00:50:03,626
First, you'll put your taste buds to the test

630
00:50:03,751 --> 00:50:08,548
- as you judge the Who-Pudding Cook-off!
- Who-Pudding Cook-off!

631
00:50:08,840 --> 00:50:10,758
- Mine first.
- I really don't know.

632
00:50:10,842 --> 00:50:12,635
No, mine's the best!

633
00:50:13,094 --> 00:50:14,554
You'll enjoy this!

634
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:17,765
This is not pudding.

635
00:50:18,599 --> 00:50:20,017
What is it?

636
00:50:20,977 --> 00:50:23,438
This is mine.
Yummy, yummy, yummy.

637
00:50:24,272 --> 00:50:26,357
Christmas Conga!

638
00:50:26,441 --> 00:50:28,818
Gee, look at the time.
I really should be getting back.

639
00:50:29,485 --> 00:50:30,778
All right!

640
00:50:36,284 --> 00:50:38,035
Fruitcake... Fa la-la!

641
00:50:38,953 --> 00:50:40,037
No.

642
00:50:45,585 --> 00:50:47,211
Fudge Judge.

643
00:50:50,131 --> 00:50:52,133
- Made it myself.
- Yeah?

644
00:50:52,216 --> 00:50:54,927
- Mine are homemade too.
- Okay.

645
00:50:55,970 --> 00:50:58,014
Put it in. Bring it on!

646
00:50:58,514 --> 00:51:00,308
Is that all you got?

647
00:51:00,391 --> 00:51:02,518
Is that all you got? Come on.

648
00:51:08,107 --> 00:51:09,484
Outta the way, slow-mo!

649
00:51:25,666 --> 00:51:28,211
He's number one in the sack race run!

650
00:51:28,294 --> 00:51:31,130
Number one! I'm number one!

651
00:51:31,506 --> 00:51:33,591
I'm number one!

652
00:51:34,175 --> 00:51:37,303
No child can beat the Grinch!

653
00:51:37,345 --> 00:51:38,513
Yeah!

654
00:51:42,391 --> 00:51:44,393
I beat you!

655
00:51:55,571 --> 00:51:59,033
And now it's time
for the moment we've all been waiting for.

656
00:51:59,075 --> 00:52:01,369
Yes! My award.

657
00:52:02,036 --> 00:52:03,704
- Write the check.
- There's no check.

658
00:52:03,788 --> 00:52:05,248
Are you sure?

659
00:52:05,331 --> 00:52:07,625
Because I really thought
I heard someone mention a check.

660
00:52:07,708 --> 00:52:08,751
I said, there's no check.

661
00:52:08,835 --> 00:52:12,088
And now it's time for Present Pass It On!

662
00:52:13,214 --> 00:52:15,883
As always, we start with our Cheermeister.

663
00:52:24,809 --> 00:52:26,769
A gift of a Christmas shave.

664
00:52:41,617 --> 00:52:43,786
Look at that hack job!

665
00:52:53,546 --> 00:52:56,340
Ah, yes, yes, yes. Good times!

666
00:52:57,925 --> 00:52:59,176
Good times.

667
00:53:00,177 --> 00:53:02,054
And now, I have a little something

668
00:53:02,096 --> 00:53:03,973
for the love of my life.

669
00:53:05,391 --> 00:53:06,976
Martha May,

670
00:53:09,437 --> 00:53:12,607
please become Mrs. Augustus May Who.

671
00:53:20,489 --> 00:53:21,991
Augustus.

672
00:53:22,992 --> 00:53:27,455
If you agree to be my wife,
along with a lifetime supply of happiness,

673
00:53:27,622 --> 00:53:29,540
you'll also receive this...

674
00:53:32,126 --> 00:53:34,795
It's a new car!

675
00:53:35,463 --> 00:53:39,091
Generously provided
by the taxpayers of Whoville!

676
00:53:41,135 --> 00:53:42,803
What do you say, Martha?

677
00:53:43,262 --> 00:53:46,182
Ya got 20 seconds on the clock.

678
00:53:48,142 --> 00:53:50,811
Well, I...

679
00:53:54,148 --> 00:53:56,901
These gifts are quite dazzling.

680
00:54:07,036 --> 00:54:09,455
Of course they are.

681
00:54:10,414 --> 00:54:12,500
That's what it's all about, isn't it?

682
00:54:12,541 --> 00:54:16,128
That's what it's always been about!

683
00:54:17,338 --> 00:54:19,924
Gifts! Gifts.

684
00:54:20,132 --> 00:54:22,426
Gifts, gifts, gifts, gifts, gifts.

685
00:54:23,427 --> 00:54:25,721
You wanna know what happens to your gifts?

686
00:54:25,805 --> 00:54:28,849
They all come to me. In your garbage.

687
00:54:29,058 --> 00:54:32,603
You see what I'm saying? In your garbage!

688
00:54:33,646 --> 00:54:38,359
I could hang myself with all the bad Christmas
neckties I found at the dump!

689
00:54:39,944 --> 00:54:41,278
And the avarice.

690
00:54:43,072 --> 00:54:46,117
The avarice never ends!

691
00:54:46,200 --> 00:54:48,703
"I want golf clubs."
"I want diamonds." "I want a pony

692
00:54:48,744 --> 00:54:52,039
"so I can ride it twice,
get bored, and sell it to make glue!"

693
00:54:52,665 --> 00:54:54,208
Look, I don't wanna make waves.

694
00:54:54,250 --> 00:54:57,795
But this whole Christmas season

695
00:54:57,878 --> 00:55:00,047
is stupid, stupid, stupid!

696
00:55:01,757 --> 00:55:03,718
There is, however,

697
00:55:04,385 --> 00:55:07,263
one teeny-tiny

698
00:55:07,722 --> 00:55:09,557
Christmas tradition

699
00:55:09,890 --> 00:55:11,392
I find

700
00:55:12,059 --> 00:55:14,895
quite meaningful.

701
00:55:20,026 --> 00:55:21,694
Mistletoe.

702
00:55:21,902 --> 00:55:24,989
Now, pucker up and kiss it, Whoville!

703
00:55:32,455 --> 00:55:36,250
Uh-oh! Somebody's fabulous!

704
00:55:39,545 --> 00:55:42,256
All right, your turn! Go on! That way!

705
00:55:49,597 --> 00:55:51,015
- Let's go!
- No!

706
00:55:51,390 --> 00:55:52,767
Excuse me, old-timer.

707
00:55:53,768 --> 00:55:55,478
Mind if I wet my whistle?

708
00:55:55,561 --> 00:55:56,937
Well...

709
00:56:00,441 --> 00:56:01,734
That's my good stuff!

710
00:56:09,950 --> 00:56:12,828
Burn, baby! Burn!

711
00:56:23,589 --> 00:56:24,840
Oh, wow.

712
00:56:25,132 --> 00:56:27,551
Oh, the Whomanity!

713
00:56:29,136 --> 00:56:30,721
- Let's go! Come on!
- No! Wait!

714
00:56:30,805 --> 00:56:32,973
- Do something.
- Right!

715
00:56:40,689 --> 00:56:42,650
Calling all units. Calling all units.

716
00:56:46,862 --> 00:56:47,988
Taxi!

717
00:56:50,241 --> 00:56:52,827
It's because I'm green, isn't it?

718
00:56:57,665 --> 00:56:58,999
Halt!

719
00:57:00,709 --> 00:57:03,170
Evening, folks. Mind if I ride along?

720
00:57:03,671 --> 00:57:05,840
You might wanna scooch over.

721
00:57:08,217 --> 00:57:09,885
You did the right thing.

722
00:57:18,102 --> 00:57:19,520
Outta the way!

723
00:57:21,230 --> 00:57:22,314
Hey!

724
00:57:29,405 --> 00:57:30,948
That's gonna hurt in the morning.

725
00:57:56,182 --> 00:57:58,309
It's gonna blow!

726
00:58:15,743 --> 00:58:19,413
You fellas all right?
Hey, how about a nice hat?

727
00:58:19,496 --> 00:58:20,623
Lou?

728
00:58:29,882 --> 00:58:31,383
I'm hurt, Lou.

729
00:58:32,426 --> 00:58:34,929
I'm hurt, and I don't hurt easily.

730
00:58:34,970 --> 00:58:37,765
But you and your family...

731
00:58:38,641 --> 00:58:40,267
I'm so...

732
00:58:40,309 --> 00:58:41,936
So disappointed.

733
00:58:43,771 --> 00:58:48,525
Can we just get back
to Christmas the way it should be?

734
00:58:49,693 --> 00:58:51,111
Grinch-less?

735
00:58:51,862 --> 00:58:54,406
Merry Christmas!

736
00:58:55,115 --> 00:58:57,451
Merry Christmas!

737
00:59:01,455 --> 00:59:05,417
I just wanted everybody
to be together for Christmas.

738
00:59:08,545 --> 00:59:12,633
I quite enjoyed that.
I hope I get another invite soon.

739
00:59:17,846 --> 00:59:19,265
Come on, come on!

740
00:59:19,306 --> 00:59:21,475
Good thing we have a spare.

741
00:59:23,644 --> 00:59:26,730
Suffering snorkelblatz!

742
00:59:27,147 --> 00:59:29,316
They're relentless!

743
00:59:34,822 --> 00:59:38,284
Only four hours till Christmas!

744
00:59:40,286 --> 00:59:42,454
Yes, the Grinch knew tomorrow

745
00:59:42,496 --> 00:59:45,916
all the Who girls and boys
would wake bright and early

746
00:59:46,000 --> 00:59:47,584
and rush for their toys.

747
00:59:47,668 --> 00:59:50,713
And then, oh, the noise!

748
00:59:50,838 --> 00:59:54,383
Oh, the noise, noise, noise, noise!

749
00:59:55,342 --> 00:59:57,344
They'll bang on tong-tinglers.

750
00:59:57,386 --> 00:59:59,847
They'll blow their floo-flounders.

751
00:59:59,888 --> 01:00:03,600
They'll crash on jang-jinglers
and bounce on boing-bounders!

752
01:00:04,476 --> 01:00:08,063
Then Whos young
and old would sit down to a feast,

753
01:00:08,147 --> 01:00:10,858
and they'll feast and they'll feast.

754
01:00:11,191 --> 01:00:14,445
And they'll feast, feast, feast, feast!

755
01:00:14,987 --> 01:00:17,031
They'll eat their Who-pudding,

756
01:00:17,197 --> 01:00:20,868
and rare Who roast beast!

757
01:00:21,368 --> 01:00:25,289
But there's something I just
cannot stand in the least.

758
01:00:25,789 --> 01:00:27,041
Oh, no.

759
01:00:27,374 --> 01:00:30,961
I'm speaking in rhyme!

760
01:00:36,091 --> 01:00:39,386
Blast you Whos!

761
01:00:43,766 --> 01:00:47,978
And the more the Grinch thought
of what Christmas would bring,

762
01:00:48,228 --> 01:00:50,564
the more the Grinch thought...

763
01:00:50,773 --> 01:00:53,484
I must stop this whole thing.

764
01:00:55,069 --> 01:00:58,906
Why, for year after year
I've put up with it now!

765
01:00:59,239 --> 01:01:01,909
I must stop this Christmas from coming!

766
01:01:01,992 --> 01:01:03,369
But how?

767
01:01:03,994 --> 01:01:06,246
I mean, in what way?

768
01:01:09,208 --> 01:01:13,337
Well, Christmas is
goin' to the dogs

769
01:01:14,963 --> 01:01:18,634
We're scarfing down
the turkey and the grog

770
01:01:25,474 --> 01:01:28,977
Are you having a holly, jolly

771
01:01:29,436 --> 01:01:31,105
Christmas?

772
01:01:32,940 --> 01:01:34,483
Wrong-o!

773
01:01:52,334 --> 01:01:54,169
If you're not going to help me,

774
01:01:54,711 --> 01:01:56,672
then you might as well...

775
01:01:57,798 --> 01:02:01,885
Then he got an idea.
An awful idea.

