You got garlic in your soul

795
01:03:24,009 --> 01:03:26,762
Mr. Grinch

796
01:03:27,262 --> 01:03:29,389
I wouldn't touch you with a

797
01:03:30,724 --> 01:03:35,729
Thirty-nine
and a half-foot pole

798
01:03:45,948 --> 01:03:49,284
I asked for three-quarters, not five-eighths.

799
01:03:49,368 --> 01:03:50,869
Stay focused!

800
01:03:57,125 --> 01:04:00,212
You know, if you asked
the Who's Who of Whoville...

801
01:04:01,838 --> 01:04:05,884
No one would deny it

802
01:04:25,279 --> 01:04:27,698
Air bag's a little slow.

803
01:04:30,200 --> 01:04:32,578
But that's what these tests are for!

804
01:04:33,620 --> 01:04:36,123
You're a vile one

805
01:04:36,164 --> 01:04:37,499
Mr. Grinch

806
01:04:38,625 --> 01:04:42,754
You have termites in your smile

807
01:04:43,297 --> 01:04:45,674
You have
all the tender sweetness

808
01:04:45,757 --> 01:04:47,843
Of a seasick crocodile

809
01:04:47,926 --> 01:04:49,970
Mr. Grinch

810
01:04:51,179 --> 01:04:54,474
Given the choice between you
I'd take the

811
01:04:54,808 --> 01:05:00,522
Seasick crocodile

812
01:05:19,916 --> 01:05:23,295
Fat boy should be finishing up anytime now.

813
01:05:24,338 --> 01:05:26,340
Talk about a recluse.

814
01:05:26,423 --> 01:05:30,844
He only comes out once a year,
and he never catches any flak for it!

815
01:05:32,137 --> 01:05:34,890
Probably lives up there to avoid the taxes.

816
01:05:36,975 --> 01:05:39,227
Merry Christmas!

817
01:05:41,188 --> 01:05:42,606
Oopsie.

818
01:05:43,732 --> 01:05:45,817
Forgot about the reindeer.

819
01:05:46,818 --> 01:05:49,446
Did that stop the old Grinch?

820
01:05:50,155 --> 01:05:51,698
No.

821
01:05:51,907 --> 01:05:54,201
The Grinch simply said...

822
01:05:54,368 --> 01:05:56,870
If I can't find a reindeer,

823
01:05:57,829 --> 01:06:00,874
I'll make one instead.

824
01:06:05,462 --> 01:06:08,965
Oh, Max!

825
01:06:12,302 --> 01:06:14,888
So he called his dog Max,

826
