854
01:08:52,337 --> 01:08:56,591
All their windows were dark.
Quiet snow filled the air.

855
01:08:56,675 --> 01:09:01,012
All the Whos were all dreaming
sweet dreams without care,

856
01:09:01,054 --> 01:09:03,890
when he came
to the first little house on the square.

857
01:09:03,974 --> 01:09:05,976
Welcome to Whoville, Max.

858
01:09:13,859 --> 01:09:15,026
Betty?

859
01:09:15,110 --> 01:09:16,570
- Betty?
- What?

860
01:09:16,653 --> 01:09:18,071
Did you hear something?

861
01:09:19,573 --> 01:09:21,867
It's Santa!

862
01:09:21,908 --> 01:09:23,827
Go right back to sleep.

863
01:09:29,291 --> 01:09:32,544
Come on, Max. It's our first stop.

864
01:09:32,836 --> 01:09:35,088
The old Grinchy Claus hissed,

865
01:09:35,130 --> 01:09:38,091
and he climbed to the roof,
empty bags in his fist.

866
01:09:38,174 --> 01:09:41,636
He'd slide down the chimney,
a rather tight pinch,

867
01:09:41,720 --> 01:09:45,140
but if Santa could do it,
then so could the Grinch.

868
01:09:45,223 --> 01:09:48,351
He's planning a double-twisting
interrupted forward-flying two-and-a-half,

869
01:09:48,435 --> 01:09:50,562
with a combo tuck and pike.

870
01:09:50,604 --> 01:09:52,272
High degree of difficulty.

871
01:10:00,363 --> 01:10:03,742
He got stuck only once,
for a moment or two.

872
01:10:03,783 --> 01:10:07,704
Blasted water weight! Goes right to my hips.

873
01:10:17,422 --> 01:10:20,800
Then he stuck
his head out of the fireplace flue.

874
01:10:21,635 --> 01:10:24,095
A little more stealth, please.

875
01:10:24,262 --> 01:10:26,806
Where the little
Who stockings all hung in a row.

876
01:10:26,890 --> 01:10:28,934
- These stockings...
- NARRATOR: He grinned.

877
01:10:28,975 --> 01:10:31,019
...are the first thing to go.

878
01:10:31,478 --> 01:10:34,064
Okay, fellas. Chow time.

879
01:11:05,679 --> 01:11:07,847
Then he slunk to the icebox.

880
01:11:09,015 --> 01:11:10,475
Slunk?

881
01:11:12,477 --> 01:11:14,562
He eyed the Whos' feast.

882
01:11:15,188 --> 01:11:17,107
He took the Who-pudding.

883
01:11:17,565 --> 01:11:19,859
He took the roast beast.

884
01:11:20,151 --> 01:11:21,403
Hike!

885
01:11:22,737 --> 01:11:24,906
He cleaned out that icebox
as quick as a flash.

886
01:11:24,990 --> 01:11:28,952
Why, that Grinch,
he even took their last can of Who-hash.

887
01:11:29,995 --> 01:11:33,456
Then he stuffed all the food
up the chimney with glee.

888
01:11:34,290 --> 01:11:37,669
- And now...
- NARRATOR: Grinned the Grinch.

889
01:11:40,046 --> 01:11:41,548
...I'll stuff up the tree.

890
