And his fib fooled the child.

912
01:13:10,762 --> 01:13:14,099
Then he patted her head,
and he got her a drink,

913
01:13:14,182 --> 01:13:16,101
and he sent her to bed.

914
01:13:24,317 --> 01:13:26,736
- Santa?
- What?

915
01:13:27,153 --> 01:13:28,613
Don't forget the Grinch.

916
01:13:30,031 --> 01:13:32,325
I know he's mean and hairy and smelly.

917
01:13:34,077 --> 01:13:36,579
His hands might be cold and clammy.

918
01:13:38,081 --> 01:13:41,751
But I think he's actually kind of sweet.

919
01:13:42,001 --> 01:13:43,044
Sweet?

920
01:13:50,760 --> 01:13:52,011
You think he's sweet?

921
01:13:53,388 --> 01:13:55,348
Merry Christmas, Santa.

922
01:14:02,230 --> 01:14:05,233
And when Cindy Lou
went up with her cup...

923
01:14:05,316 --> 01:14:06,651
Nice kid.

924
01:14:07,902 --> 01:14:09,863
Bad judge of character.

925
01:14:11,614 --> 01:14:14,576
...he went to the chimney
and stuffed the tree up.

926
01:14:22,542 --> 01:14:25,837
And the last thing he took
was the log for their fire.

927
01:14:25,879 --> 01:14:29,883
On their walls he left nothing
but some hooks and some wire.

928
01:14:30,300 --> 01:14:33,052
And the one speck of food
that he'd left in the house,

929
01:14:33,094 --> 01:14:36,931
