It started in low, then it started to grow.

1005
01:22:59,183 --> 01:23:01,686
But the sound wasn't sad.

1006
01:23:02,311 --> 01:23:04,772
Why, this sounded merry.

1007
01:23:05,898 --> 01:23:09,068
But it was merry. Very.

1008
01:23:09,902 --> 01:23:13,572
Every Who down in Whoville,
the tall and the small,

1009
01:23:13,864 --> 01:23:17,118
were singing without any presents at all.

1010
01:23:23,165 --> 01:23:27,086
He hadn't stopped Christmas
from coming. It came.

1011
01:23:27,169 --> 01:23:30,589
Somehow or other, it came just the same!

1012
01:23:34,301 --> 01:23:35,720
Mr. Grinch?

1013
01:23:38,723 --> 01:23:42,435
And the Grinch,
with his Grinch feet ice-cold in the snow,

1014
01:23:42,476 --> 01:23:45,479
stood puzzling and puzzling.

1015
01:23:45,646 --> 01:23:47,440
How could it be so?

1016
01:23:48,065 --> 01:23:50,025
It came without ribbons!

1017
01:23:50,317 --> 01:23:52,153
It came without tags!

1018
01:23:52,945 --> 01:23:56,365
It came without packages, boxes or bags!

1019
01:23:59,326 --> 01:24:02,121
And he puzzled and puzzled,

1020
01:24:02,246 --> 01:24:04,290
till his puzzler was sore.

1021
01:24:07,168 --> 01:24:10,755
Then the Grinch thought of something

1022
01:24:11,088 --> 01:24:12,715
he hadn't before.

1023
01:24:13,132 --> 01:24:16,510
Maybe Christmas...

1024
01:24:16,802 --> 01:24:18,179
He thought.

1025
01:24:21,098 --> 01:24:24,727
...doesn't come from a store.

1026
01:24:28,564 --> 01:24:30,149
Maybe Christmas,

1027
01:24:31,567 --> 01:24:32,860
perhaps,

1028
01:24:38,824 --> 01:24:41,160
means a little bit more.

1029
01:25:13,025 --> 01:25:14,235
Max!

1030
01:25:14,693 --> 01:25:16,195
Help me!

1031
01:25:17,071 --> 01:25:18,280
I'm

1032
